race.comment: NATSUKO (1) finds it hard to break through. Has finished in the placings two on end now, the latest when third (33.46) at Muswellbrook. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Makes plenty of appeal. BENTLEY FISHER (7) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 3.5 lengths at this track in a handy 24.80 beating Indi's Girl. Has never been out of the placings from two starts out of this box. Leading chance again. ARCTIC IMAGE (8) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fifth (23.29) in a Grade 5 at Dubbo. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from three attempts. One of the main contenders. RORY ROGUE (4) is a last-start placegetter when at the top of betting - in the mix again.
